subSubSection.paragraph:
Variability.
Genital morphology shows variability in females (
Fig. 5 A–F
). The inner lobe can be wider as in LX1981, LX1974 (
Fig. 5 A–B
) and less abruptly curved as in LX1981 (
Fig. 5 B–D
). The outer lobe can be shorter and can point ventrally as in LX1981, LX1974 (
Fig. 5 E–F
). The outer lobe can be hidden by the inner lobe in a dorsal view as in LX1981 (
Fig. 5 B
).
